  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Nelson Mandela, the leading opponent of South Africa's white-led government was freed after 27 years in prison on 11 February 1990.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   From prison he had led the fight against the government's policy of racial segregation, apartheid.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   He was convicted in 1964 of conspiracy
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   to overthrow the government and sentenced to life in prison.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   International pressure had been mounting for his release and many governments had imposed sanctions on South Africa.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   He continued the fight for black human rights after his release, but had many problems
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   to overcome including factional fighting between the ANC and the Zulu Inkatha group.
  </a>
